Retail Technology Consulting
A leading technology consultancy to the retail industry, we help clients re-invent in-store
                        experiences by combining the beauty of shopping with the best technologies.
We use technology expertly and wisely making is easy for shoppers to find, explore, try on,
                        taste, enjoy and
                        buy products in stores.
"The Top Idea in Retail Innovation"




Technology Incubator/Store
We own a popular retail store in Seattle, were we continuously experiment with a vast array of
                        technologies, measuring their impact on customer experience and sales.
Most of our experiments fail to deliver benefits, but a few work surprisingly well and we turn
                        those into scalable solutions for our clients.
"Hointer Shop Tailored to Digital Age"




Adaptable Technology
Over years we built and programmed many in-store technologies, including IoT devices, robotics,
                        magic displays, eTags, iBeacons, instant checkout and others.
We re-use those modules as building blocks to skillfully and inexpensively develop new shopping
                        experiences for our clients from pilots to rollouts.
"High-tech Shopping at Hointer"







Increase in-store sales and lower your cost structure





Hointer changed the dressing room experience
                    completely with an iPad
                    interface that avoids awkward associate interactions and makes use of automated micro-warehouses.
                    And
                    the impact was significant with 6x more items tried on, while cross-product recommendations led to
                    an
                    80% increase in sales.











Hointer became an end-to-end solution for
                    retail stores—digitized
                    product information, smart fitting rooms and streamlined backroom operations, enabling customers to
                    browse
                    easily and try on a larger selection of clothes. It also allowed sales associates to use customer
                    and
                    product data to make personalized recommendations.
                    The result: improved customer experiences, higher sales and fewer returns.











 In addition to the streamlined digitized experience,
                    Hointer
                    technology
                    also reduces the need for shelf and floor space and opens up new modes of attractive product
                        presentation.
                











 As both a technology and retailer innovator — not unlike Amazon!
                    —
                    Hointer is educating its shoppers to shop in a different way with different
                    norms and different
                    expectations. The product of that education is not just a more sophisticated Hointer shopper, but a
                    shopper who may now become impatient with the delays, inefficiencies, and inferior experiences
                    proffered
                    by other retailers. That’s where value-added differentiation and competitive advantage come
                        from.
                












Hointer is truly a quintessential example of the convergence of the art and
                    science of retailing.
                











Hointer improves showroom density by 60% -
                    microwarehouse improve space utilization in stores by reducing the number of each item that must be
                    displayed on the floor. How big of a difference does it make? In a recent test with Macy’s, Hointer
                    was able to optimize the floor space and showcase 60% more styles on the showroom floor.
                    Furthermore, because customers don’t have to rummage through inventory for their size, associates
                    spend less time refreshing displays and more time helping customers.
                












