Nadia Shouraboura,

Founder & CEO, Hointer

Follow @NShouraboura









Dr. Nadia Shouraboura is the founder and CEO of Hointer, a business that is reinventing the shopping experience. In 1987, Shouraboura began her career, after emigrating from Russia to Israel, as a software developer working on computer aided design systems for industrial robotics. During her Ph.D. work at Princeton University, Nadia performed research at AT&T Bell Labs and co-founded Starlight Multimedia, a developer of multi-media applications. Shouraboura joined Amazon.com in March of 2004. As technology vice president of Amazon’s Worldwide Operations, she owned technology powering Amazon’s global supply chain and fulfillment. Shouraboura also served on Jeff Bezos’ senior leadership team responsible for overall direction and operations of Amazon.














